μ. τῇ διαθήκῃ “POxy.” 494.33 (2nd c.AD), etc. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> with <i>accusative</i> <i>of things</i>, <b>testify to</b> a thing, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 7th-6th c.BC: Alcaeus Lyricus 102, 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 13.108, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 515, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedrus” 244d; μ. τινί τι 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 6.21, 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Supplices” 797 (Lyric poetry). \">Refs 7th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> μ. περί τινος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Apologia” 21a; ὑπέρ τινος 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 29.54. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__5</b></Level3> with <i>infinitive</i>, <b>testify that</b> a thing is, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD(?): Heraclitus 34, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 1265, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τίς σοι μαρτυρήσει ταῦτ᾽ ἐμοῦ κλύει; <b>that</b> he heard.. ? [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Tr.” 422, compare 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hippolytus” 977; ὁ κληθεὶς μαρτυρείτω ἀληθῆ μαρτυρεῖν “PHal.” 1.225 (3rd c.BC)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: rarely with <i>participle</i>, μαρτυρεῖτέ [μοι].. ῥινηλατούσῃ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 1184; μ. τισὶ παραγινομέναις 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis 8.46. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__6</b></Level3> μ. τινὶ ὡς.. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 494, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Gorgias” 523c; σώματα.. ὡς ἔστιν, αὐτὴ ἡ αἴσθησις.. μ. 4th-3rd c.BC: Epicurus Philosophus “Epistulae” 1p.6U. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; μ. ὅτι.. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “de Vectigalibus” 4.25. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__7</b></Level3> μ. τινὶ τῆς συμμαχίας <b>testify to, acknowledge t